.TH "KENNEL-BIN-INIT" "8" "" "Project Kennel" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kennel\-bin\-init \- trusted uid\-0 PID 1 inside a kennel
.SH SYNOPSIS
(internal \(em forked by kenneld(8), not invoked directly)
.SH DESCRIPTION
kennel\-bin\-init is the kennel's PID 1: a trusted, root\-owned binary the privhelper factory fexecves after pivot_root. It makes no policy decisions \(em it pulls a supervision plan from kenneld over binder and executes it verbatim, forking the facades and the workload and reaping them.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBkenneld\fR(8), \fBkennel\fR(1)
